ard.com/uprojectorion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>projectorion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Nuclear Renaissance Man</span><br>  Posts: 1592<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(7/4/02 11:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=261.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Nuclear Fighter Bombers?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://a1016.g.akamai.net/f/1016/606/1d/image.pathfinder.com/popsci/images/space/space0702smarterbombers_E.gif"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<br>
A proposal to transform the F-22 Raptor into a high-altitude, first-strike bomber illustrates a harsh reality: The U.S. bombing fleet is ill-prepared to fight wars in regions that are short on friendly nations willing to lend air bases.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.popsci.com/popsci/aviation/article/0,12543,262063,00.html">Source: Popular Science.</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
Turning a fighter into a bomber may seem like trying to convert a Honda S2000 roadster into a pickup truck. Fighters, which are designed to dogfight with hostile airplanes and perform short-range attack missions, are fast and agile; bombers are made to haul heavy loads for thousands of miles. But Lockheed Martin is designing a fighter-bomber hybrid based on the F-22 Raptor fighter that's in flight-testing at Edwards Air Force Base in California. The proposed bomber variant—informally known as the FB-22—has been attracting increasing interest since the September 11 attacks and the start of U.S. operations in Afghanistan. <br>
##############################################<br>
I recall a conversation about reactor powered aircraft and it was suggested that if possible, such a fighter would not necessarily be faster than a chemical powered jet but could attain twice the range. I didn't realise at the time what a great advantage this was. Such aircraft would make conventional fighters useless.    <br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/uarkuunaves.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ArkuunAves</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Space Tourist</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(7/17/02 1:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=261.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Nuclear Fighter Bombers?</span><hr size=1> eh, I think that both the idea of needing reactor-powered planes, as well as trying to convert F-22 stealth aircraft into high-altitude bombers, are unneccessary.<br>
<br>
There is no lack of long-range bombers in the US arsenal.  One must consider the fact that what is left of our B-52 StratCom force alone could decimate most small nations in a few passes.<br>
<br>
Then throw in B-1, B-2, and F-117 craft.<br>
<br>
2 further things to keep in mind, after all of those craft:<br>
<br>
1)Aerial refueling, which has become standard practice in many conflicts, and allowed a B-52 strike mission in the opening phases of Desert Storm where the B-52s started their flight in the US(Iowa? Idaho?  I forget which).  That's quite a range.<br>
<br>
2)Submarines.  We'll be surging new guided missile subs that are refitted Ohio-class boomers modified to carry 154 Block-IV Tomahawks instead of nukes.  The Block-IV, in case yer like most people and don't know, is capable of launching and flying a preset route for up to a few hours, and then being uplinked final target coordinates that it homes in on.  Roughly translated-if you're within a couple hours flight-time at cruising speed for a Tomahawk from a body of water, yer screwed.<br>
<br>
<br>
I don't anticipate any major strategic problems which require drastic modifications to anything anytime soon =)  do you? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/uzaphod4468.showPublicProfile?language=EN>zaphod4468</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br>  Posts: 628<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(7/17/02 9:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=261.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.bbc.co.uk/cult/hitchhikers/gallery/images/100/zaphod2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Nuclear Fighter Bombers?</span><hr size=1> History Channel had a program on SAC last night... After aerial refueling was put into practice<br>
they flew a B-52 all the way around the world, non-stop in something like 90 hours. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=atomicconspiracy>Atomic Conspiracy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 162<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(7/18/02 1:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=261.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Nuclear Fighter Bombers?</span><hr size=1> It was 45 hours, <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.aero-web.org/history/events/images/opfdfc57.htm">Operation Power Flight</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->. <br>
I had a tough time understanding the F-22 article. It cites the loss of overseas bases as a reason for this F-22 bomber program, but the <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://home.att.net/~jbaugher4/f22_1.html">F-22</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->, in fact, has a considerably shorter unrefuelled range than any of the 3 current strategic bombers. The lack of both standup headroom and the prosaic but vital facility of an onboard toilet would also limit its endurance even with air refuelling.     <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/uarkuunaves.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ArkuunAves</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Space Tourist</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(7/18/02 6:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=261.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Nuclear Fighter Bombers?</span><hr size=1> I'm definitely in agreement here.  The practicalities of trying to use a craft like the F-22 for long-range,high-altitude bombing seem pretty dim.<br>
<br>
Aside from previously stated issues, the other issue to arise will be crew reliability.  You're asking a lone pilot with piloting, navigation, and payload delivery on missions that could last more than a full day?  I hold the utmost respect for the capabilities of US pilots, but even with that respect I don't think I'd want to rely on a group of 12 or so pilots that have been awake and at battle-ready status for 20 hours to deliver their payload and avoid detection on the way out.<br>
<br>
It would seem to me the US will end end sticking with the other proven weapons we've developed specifically for these missions, rather than try to poorly adapt a new technology to it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/utmayes1965.showPublicProfile?language=EN>tmayes1965</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Space Cadet</span><br>  Posts: 41<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(7/19/02 2:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=261.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Nuclear Fighter Bombers?</span><hr size=1> Our aircraft carrier based jets,, and our nuclear submarines can hit any target we need to destroy  any where on the planet. Land bases are not required to achieve this.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/uyales.showPublicProfile?language=EN>yales</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>MegaLipidCephaloid</span><br>  Posts: 370<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(7/19/02 8:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=261.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.attbi.com/~yales/images/53invad2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Nuclear Fighter Bombers?</span><hr size=1> This post was deleted before, but perhaps I may be allowed to post this now.<br>
<br>
