A fighter-bomber would be the least likely type of vehicle to use with a reactor.<br>
<br>
1) The enormous mass of the reactor and the enormous mass of the shielding would make it a lumbering ox.<br>
<br>
2) The Project Pluto ramjet was the size and mass of a railroad engine (and it carried no shielding)<br>
<br>
3) Field maintanance would be a nightmare - vast torrents of lethal penetrating radiation and dealing with the required cooling needs from decay heat. Imagine dealing with parking planes that will kill any unprotected person on the base.<br>
<br>
4) A crash by accident or in combat would spew huge quantities of fallout. A SAM exploding a reactor in the air is a chilling thought. A terrorist with a Stinger could contaminate much a a country.<br>
<br>
5) Throttling of a reactor is a gradual process, the opposite of a fighter's needs in a dogfight.<br>
<br>
6) reactors are fabuously expensive, and require specialized technicians.<br>
